# Glossary
> **Post**: The field that has a pinned map location and a story with detailed publish time, mentioned time and tag.  
> **Guest User**: A person who can only browse the site.  
> **Registered User**: A person who can post, comment, like and annotate on any written subject on the page.  
> **Admin**: A person who manages the site and has all the privileges.  
> **Profile Page**: The private page of the user.  
> **Profile Picture**: A picture belongs to the user.  
> **Header Picture**: A second picture which is covered back on the profile picture as in Facebook.  
> **Profile Description**: A text which tells about the user and edited by the user.  
> **Memory**: A post that consists of memory items.  
> **Memory Item**: A text or multimedia related to a person's history or recollection.  
> **Post**: The field that has a pinned map location and a story with detailed publish time, mentioned time and tag.  
> **Tag**: The information that gives a general idea about the post. Tags are used to make relations between posts.  
> **Story**: Every post has a story which tells us about the history related to the post.  
> **Description**: Information that gives general explanation about the post.  
> **Mentioned Time**: The time when the memory event took place or the time the memory is about.  
> **Recommendation**: Tags will be used for recommendations to be adjusted for the user.  
> **Pinned map**: The map in which has pins about the posts and users's story.  
> **Location**: Existence of the user whereby adding his/her geographical position.  
> **Multimedia**: Any type of recorded file especially in the format of mp3 or mp4.  
> **Annotate**: To footnote to any relevant information.  
> **Comment**: Users ideas about relevant posts.  
> **Homepage**: The root page in the application for users.  
> **Ban**: A permanent suspension of a registered user.  
> **System**: Operative background of the application which is hidden from the users.  
> **Google Maps API**: Data gives you accurate real-time information for mapping, navigation and places. about relevant posts.  
> **Database**: A database is an organized collection of data.  
> **Response Time**: System's answer time to a request.  
> **System Runtime**: The amount of time which a system is up online.


# 1. Functional Requirements
> ## 1.1. User Requirements 
* ### 1.1.1. Guest User
  * **1.1.1.1.** Guest Users shall be able to see and browse accounts.
  * **1.1.1.2.** Guest Users shall be able to search for memories.
  * **1.1.1.3.** Guest Users shall be able to see memories.
    * **1.1.1.3.1.** Guest Users should be able to see annotations, comments and number of likes on a memory.
  * **1.1.1.4. Registration**
    * **1.1.1.4.1.** Guest Users shall be able to register an account.
    * **1.1.1.4.1.** Users shall register with a unique handle.
* ### 1.1.2 Registered User
  * **1.1.2.1.** Registered Users shall be able to login to their accounts.
  * **1.1.2.2. Profile Customization** 
    * **1.1.2.2.1.** Registered Users should be able to set their profile pictures.
    * **1.1.2.2.2.** Registered Users should be able to set their header pictures.
    * **1.1.2.2.3.** Registered Users should be able to add a description to their profile pages.
    * **1.1.2.2.4.** Registered Users should be able to set the colour scheme of their profile pages.
  * **1.1.2.3.** Registered Users shall be able to see and browse accounts.
  * **1.1.2.4.** Registered Users shall be able to search for memory items.
    * **1.1.2.4.1.** Registered Users shall be able to search by text.
    * **1.1.2.4.2.** Registered Users should be able to search by location.
    * **1.1.2.4.3.** Registered Users should be able to search by mentioned time.
  * **1.1.2.5. Memory Items and Memories**
    * **1.1.2.5.1.** Registered Users shall be able see memories.
    * **1.1.2.5.2.** Registered Users shall be able to post memories.
      * **1.1.2.5.2.1** The user shall be able to add a description to the memory.
      * **1.1.2.5.2.2** The user shall be able to add a story to the memory.
      * **1.1.2.5.2.3** The user shall be able to add a mentioned time to the memory.
      * **1.1.2.5.2.4** The user shall be able to add a description to the memory.
      * **1.1.2.5.2.5** The user shall be able to add a location to the memory.
      * **1.1.2.5.2.6** The user shall be able to add multimedia to the memory.
      * **1.1.2.5.2.7** The user shall be able to add tags to the memory.
    * **1.1.2.5.3.** Registered Users shall be able to annotate a story, a description or multimedia. 
      * **1.1.2.5.3.** Multimedia contents shall be viewed within page.   
    * **1.1.2.5.4.** Registered Users shall be able to see annotations, comments and number of likes on a memory.
    * **1.1.2.5.5.** Registered Users shall be able to leave a comment on memories.
    * **1.1.2.5.6.** Registered Users shall be able to like memories.
  * **1.1.2.6** Registered Users shall be able to see recommendations.
  * **1.1.2.7 Homepage**
    * **1.1.2.7.1** Registered Users shall be able to view a pinned map. 
    * **1.1.2.7.1** Registered Users shall be able to view recent posts. 
    * **1.1.2.7.1** Registered Users shall be able to view trending posts.
* ### 1.1.3 Admin
  * **1.1.3.1** Admins shall be able to delete content.
    * **1.1.3.1.1.** Admins shall be able to delete memories.
    * **1.1.3.1.2.** Admins should be able to delete comments.
    * **1.1.3.1.3.** Admins should be able to delete annotations.
  * **1.1.3.2** Admins shall be able to ban or delete accounts.

> ## 1.2. The System Requirements
* ### 1.2.1. API
  * **1.2.1.1.** System shall use Google Maps API to view the pinned map.
* ### 1.2.2. Database
  * **1.2.2.1.** System shall have a Database to keep all the data about posts.
* ### 1.2.3. Recommendations
  * **1.2.3.1.** System shall be able to give recommendations about related content to the user.
    * **1.2.3.1.1.** These recommendations should be based on the tags. 
    * **1.2.3.1.2.** These recomandations should be based on the previous searches of the user.
* ### 1.2.4. Types of Users
  * **1.2.4.1.** System shall have different types of users
    * **1.2.4.1.1.** System shall have Admin to moderate the posts.
    * **1.2.4.1.2.** System shall have Users to generate new posts.
    * **1.2.4.1.3.** System shall have Guest to view existing content to visitor.
* ### 1.2.5. Posts and Annotation
  * **1.2.5.1.** System shall allow users to annotate images or texts which will be used for further enhancements to the system.
  * **1.2.5.2.** System should decide on the sorting order of comments based on the likes.
  * **1.2.5.3.** System shall require information about the posts.

# 2.Non-Functional Requirements
* ## 2.1. Performance
  * **2.1.1.** The system shall work with number of registered user without crashing.
  * **2.1.2.** Response time for a request should be less than 2 seconds.
* ## 2.2 Security
  * **2.2.1.** The application shall be secure against various attacks
     * **2.2.1.1.** Passwords of all users will be stored encrypted
* ## 2.3 Compatibility
  * **2.3.1.** The system shall be compatible with Android 4.4(Kitkat) or upper versions(94.3% of android device).
  * **2.3.2.** The system shall be compatible with Google Chrome, Firefox, Safari.
  * **2.3.3.** The system shall arrange the content size as compatible for different platforms.
* ## 2.4 Reliability
  * **2.4.1.** The system runtime should be greater than %98 of the time.
  * **2.4.2.** A database structure shall be formed and used in the application
  * **2.4.3.** The system shall back up its database every week.
* ## 2.5 Annotations
  * **2.5.1.** The annotations shall be designed according to W3C format 
  * **2.5.2.** The annotations shall be stored in JSON format



    
